A giant crane broke free from a skyscraper, crashing into residential buildings on Manhattan's East Side, resulting in at least two deaths.
Residents had raised concerns about the construction site's safety practices.
Mayor Bloomberg confirmed four fatalities and multiple injuries, labeling it one of the city's worst construction accidents.
The incident occurred during a crane maneuver, causing structural failure.
Rescue efforts were underway to locate survivors amidst the rubble.
Despite the tragedy, residents expressed relief that it happened on a weekend with fewer people around.
The city's reliance on cranes was evident as workers used other cranes to stabilize the fallen one.
